d on the numerous women's names ending in <i>-ice</i>."]},{"name":"Annys","meanings":["and English: a medieval vernacular form of   Agnes  , which gave rise to a surname. Its modern use as a given name is probably at least in part a transferred use of the surname as well as a revival of the medieval given name."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705207,"age":1,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":3,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":16,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Annis Littlecoate was born about 1584, in Downton, Wiltshire, England. She married Ebenezer William Cookney on 10 September 1605, in Downton, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died about 1613, 